<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,834,1903]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2016" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2016" box="[593,896,1014,1039]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuhapimuk">
<emphasis box="[593,746,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">P. kuhapimuk</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber" box="[755,896,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" refString="Huber, B. A., Petcharad, B., Leh, M. U., C., Koh, J. K. H. &amp; Ghazali, A. R. M. (2016) The Southeast Asian Pholcus halabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae): new data from field observations and ultrastructure. European Journal of Taxonomy, 190, 1 - 55. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.190" type="journal article" year="2016">
Huber, 
<number box="[840,896,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2016.0">2016</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber" box="[959,1165,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" refString="Huber, B. A., Petcharad, B., Leh, M. U., C., Koh, J. K. H. &amp; Ghazali, A. R. M. (2016) The Southeast Asian Pholcus halabala species group (Araneae, Pholcidae): new data from field observations and ultrastructure. European Journal of Taxonomy, 190, 1 - 55. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.190" type="journal article" year="2016">
Huber 
<emphasis box="[1038,1089,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1105,1165,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2016.0">2016</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1178,1208,1015,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="17.0">17</number>
, figs 
<number box="[1273,1303,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="49.0">49</number>
–51, 58–62, 96– 
<number box="[196,225,1050,1075]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="98.0">98</number>
), in having a similar uncus (
<figureCitation box="[547,629,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[600,629,1051,1075]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
C), appendix (
<figureCitation box="[790,872,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[843,872,1051,1075]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
C), and female genetalia (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1248,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Figs 
<number box="[1221,1248,1051,1075]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B) but can be easily distinguished by the presence of a large, blunt dorsal flap subdistally on the procursus (arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[1325,1405,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,195,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[221,1365,195,1878]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male. A – B. Pedipalp (A. Prolateral view, arrow points at large, blunt dorsal flap on procursus; B. Retrolateral view, arrow points at indistinct retrolatero-dorsal apophysis); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C. Prolateral view; D. Retrolateral view). a = appendix, b = bulb, e = embolus, pr = procursus, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.10 (A – B), 0.03 (C – D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260717/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[1378,1405,1087,1111]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A) and by the absence of sclerotized ventral apophyses subproximally on the procursus (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1188,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,195,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[221,1365,195,1878]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male. A – B. Pedipalp (A. Prolateral view, arrow points at large, blunt dorsal flap on procursus; B. Retrolateral view, arrow points at indistinct retrolatero-dorsal apophysis); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C. Prolateral view; D. Retrolateral view). a = appendix, b = bulb, e = embolus, pr = procursus, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.10 (A – B), 0.03 (C – D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260717/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[1159,1188,1123,1147]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,834,1903]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,566,1158,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus box="[443,552,1158,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 
<number box="[739,788,1159,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="3.83">3.83</number>
(
<number box="[812,863,1159,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="4.09">4.09</number>
with clypeus), carapace 
<number box="[1173,1222,1159,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1.14">1.14</number>
long, 
<number box="[1310,1359,1158,1183]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1.25">1.25</number>
wide, opisthosoma 
<number box="[301,350,1194,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2.69">2.69</number>
long, 
<number box="[425,474,1195,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.94">0.94</number>
wide. Leg I, leg II and leg III missing, leg IV: 
<number box="[1021,1084,1194,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="28.15">28.15</number>
(
<number box="[1101,1151,1195,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="8.33">8.33</number>
+ 
<number box="[1185,1234,1194,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.52">0.52</number>
+ 
<number box="[1267,1316,1194,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="6.54">6.54</number>
+ 
<number box="[1349,1411,1194,1219]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="11.67">11.67</number>
+ 
<number box="[151,204,1231,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1.09">1.09</number>
). Distance PME-PME 
<number box="[483,535,1231,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.28">0.28</number>
; diameter PME 
<number box="[740,791,1231,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.11">0.11</number>
; distance PME-ALE 
<number box="[1053,1106,1230,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.06">0.06</number>
; distance AME-AME 
<number box="[1379,1431,1231,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.03">0.03</number>
; diameter AME 
<number box="[333,386,1267,1291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.07">0.07</number>
. Sternum wider than long (
<number box="[708,760,1266,1291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.84">0.84</number>
/ 
<number box="[769,821,1266,1291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="0.66">0.66</number>
). Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1009,1082,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1365,193,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pholcus tharnlodensis sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, e = embolus, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.07 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260708/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Figs 
<number box="[1068,1082,1267,1291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E–F. Carapace yellowish, with brown marks; sternum yellowish, with brown marks posteriorly, ocular area yellowish. Legs yellowish, patellae, distal parts of tibiae and proximal parts of metatarsi dark brown, darker rings absent. Opisthosoma pale brown dorsally, yellowish ventrally. Ocular area elevated; each eye triad on top of a short, laterally directed eye-stalk (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[183,380,1411,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhuchuandiani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[183,380,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">P. zhuchuandiani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[390,484,1410,1435]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[390,484,1410,1435]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, cf. 
<figureCitation box="[541,625,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[210,1373,195,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[210,1373,195,1906]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 31. Male and female ocular area, frontal view. A – B. Pholcus tharnlodensis sp. nov., holotype male (A) and paratype female (B). C – D. P. hinsonensis sp. nov., holotype male (C) and paratype female (D). E – F. P. zhuchuandiani sp. nov., holotype male (E) and paratype female (F). Scale bars: 0.10 (A – F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260735/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[596,625,1411,1435]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Thoracic furrow absent. Chelicerae as in 
<figureCitation box="[1153,1236,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[1208,1236,1411,1435]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
D, with a pair of proximo-lateral apophyses, a pair of black distal apophyses, each with two teeth, and a pair of indistinct frontal apophyses. Pedipalps as in 
<figureCitation box="[463,547,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,195,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[221,1365,195,1878]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male. A – B. Pedipalp (A. Prolateral view, arrow points at large, blunt dorsal flap on procursus; B. Retrolateral view, arrow points at indistinct retrolatero-dorsal apophysis); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C. Prolateral view; D. Retrolateral view). a = appendix, b = bulb, e = embolus, pr = procursus, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.10 (A – B), 0.03 (C – D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260717/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Figs 
<number box="[520,547,1483,1507]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B; trochanter with a long ventral apophysis; femur with a dorsal apophysis retrolaterally; procursus simple proximally but complex distally, with a large, blunt dorsal flap subdistally (arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[151,240,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,195,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[221,1365,195,1878]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male. A – B. Pedipalp (A. Prolateral view, arrow points at large, blunt dorsal flap on procursus; B. Retrolateral view, arrow points at indistinct retrolatero-dorsal apophysis); C – D. Distal part of procursus (C. Prolateral view; D. Retrolateral view). a = appendix, b = bulb, e = embolus, pr = procursus, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.10 (A – B), 0.03 (C – D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260717/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,240,1555,1579]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A); uncus sclerotized proximally but membranous distally; appendix curved with scales; embolus sclerotized, with some transparent projections distally. Legs with short vertical setae on tibiae, metatarsi and tarsi; without spines and curved setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,834,1903]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1662,1687]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Female:</emphasis>
Similar to male, habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[637,719,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
Figs 
<number box="[692,719,1663,1687]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="14.0">14</number>
