<figureCitation box="[884,965,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[221,1364,193,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[221,1365,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 14. Pholcus ballarini sp. nov., holotype male (C – F) and paratype female (A – B, G – H). A. External genitalia, ventral view; B. Vulva, dorsal view; C. Bulbal apophyses, prolateral view; D. Chelicerae, frontal view; E – H. Habitus (E, G. Dorsal view; F, H. Ventral view). a = appendix, da = distal apophysis, e = embolus, fa = frontal apophysis, pa = proximo-lateral apophysis, pp = pore plate, u = uncus. Scale bars: 0.05 (A – C), 0.10 (D), 0.50 (E – H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260718/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
